Here's how to wire all three requirements together:

**1. Custom back button via `BackButtonBehavior`** — set it in your page constructor or XAML:

```xml
<!-- EditProductPage.xaml -->
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage">
    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior
            TextOverride="Cancel"
            Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <!-- ... your form ... -->
</ContentPage>
```

**2 & 3. Intercept navigation and confirm** — handle both the custom button *and* the hardware/gesture back:

```csharp
// EditProductPage.xaml.cs
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    public bool HasUnsavedChanges { get; set; }

    public ICommand BackCommand { get; }

    public EditProductPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BackCommand = new Command(async () => await TryGoBack());
        BindingContext = this;
    }

    // Intercepts Android hardware back & swipe-back gestures
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (HasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            // Fire-and-forget the dialog; return true to cancel navigation now
            _ = TryGoBack();
            return true;   // true = "I handled it, don't navigate"
        }

        return false;       // false = default back behavior
    }

    private async Task TryGoBack()
    {
        if (HasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave) return; // user chose Stay — cancel navigation
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

**How it works:**

| Trigger | Handler |
|---|---|
| Custom "Cancel" button tap | `BackCommand` → `TryGoBack()` |
| Android hardware back / swipe | `OnBackButtonPressed()` → `TryGoBack()` |

**Caveats:**
- `OnBackButtonPressed` fires on Android only. On iOS, `BackButtonBehavior.Command` replaces the default chevron, so the custom button path covers it.
- Set `HasUnsavedChanges = true` whenever a form field changes (e.g., via property setters or `TextChanged` events).
